Erollisi Marr <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=def44106>def44106</A> at: 6/11/01 7:09:54 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 7:52:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help a level 17 Wizard out with advice....</span><hr size=1> 1.  Learning to kite at 17 is possible, but requires a constant source of Sow.  Without sow, it cannot be done till level 29 and you get Bonds of Force (snare).  Also see answer to question 5.<br>
<br>
2.  First get a Shiny Metallic Robe.  Sells for about 4000pp.  Couple bat fang earings (500pp each), +7 int +7 str necklass (400-500pp), Ring of frots (not sure on value).  For weapon slots, get Stien of mogguk for off hand (100-150pp), Black Tome with Silver Runes for Primary (200-250pp), and Students Homework (not sure on value, but back when I got mine it was around 1-2K).  <br>
<br>
3.  See answer to question 5<br>
<br>
4.  Places to go.  Hmm, at 17, check out Lake Rathe Aviak Guards.  Good xp, but always camped.  Lake of Ill Omen is WAY over camped (which can be a good thing if your wanting to kite).  Oasis is ok, but also over camped.  South Ro might be best bet.  Get into a Aviak Group and let the xp flow.  <br>
<br>
5.  Here are some sites with GREAT wizard related information:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/or2/Wizards/">www.angelfire.com/or2/Wizards/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://perso.wanadoo.fr/nicolbolas/englishindex.html">perso.wanadoo.fr/nicolbol...index.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cumdar>Cumdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 10:05:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help a level 17 Wizard out with advice....</span><hr size=1> I just popped 24 the other day.  Kiting can be tough at our level make sure you are sowed but it can be done.  I kited griffawns in NK for practice at about your level.<br>
<br>
HH Pass is a good place to learn to group at your level.  I don't suggest learning to group in Ill Omen.  HH Pass also has another advantage over Ill Omen:  the people there are fair as far as letting people into the groups.  They will usually list people.  In Ill Omen, it seems as though the only time I get into a group is when someone has an alt that is a wiz and they know that people don't pick us up for groups as well as others.  Once I do get into a group people are surprised at how good I really am.  I have made many friends in Ill Omen and the xp is awesome.  You will also get more runes for research in Ill Omen than any other zone I have run accross.<br>
<br>
Oh, yeah almost forgot.  Oasis stinks.  you can get good XP there.  But then someone lets a spectre loose or a Sand Giant gets mad and comes by and kills you for no reason.  I tried fighting there.  I would fight for 2 hours and then lose all my xp I gained by getting slaughtered by a MOB 20+ over my level.  That stinks.<br>
<br>
Have fun and be safe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uquinnell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quinnell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 12:52:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help a level 17 Wizard out with advice....</span><hr size=1> The hunting advice was solid.<br>
<br>
One thing I'd add -- with that amount of cash, I'd look into purchasing an EE bag (400-500pp) and maybe another weight reducing bag....<br>
<br>
you'll appreciate it later. <p>Chaos, Panic and Disorder?  My work here is done.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/01 9:12:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help a level 17 Wizard out with advice....</span><hr size=1> Equipment to look for assuming you are nekid -<br>
<br>
1. Crystalline robe (+6 int 10mana) 1000pp<br>
2. pair of batskull earrings (+10 int) 800pp for pair<br>
3. braided cinch cord (+4int) 400pp<br>
4. polished bone bracers (+6int) 200pp for pair<br>
5. gatorscale sleeves (+4int) 400pp<br>
6. white scaled legs (+2 int) 400pp<br>
7. sheer bone mask (+3int) 300pp<br>
8. ring of frost (+3int 10mana)  100pp<br>
9. rose velium ring (+5int) 800pp<br>
10. night shade wreath (+5int) 500pp<br>
11. kunzar cloak (+2int) 300pp<br>
12. embroidered black cape (+20mana) 300pp<br>
13. crystal line slippers (+3 int) 1200pp<br>
14. black tome w/silver runes (+4 int 30mana) 400pp<br>
15. stein of magokk (+10 int) 250pp<br>
16. students homework (+3int 15mana) 1000pp<br>
<br>
8350pp for +70 int and +85 mana should get you into your 40s before you need to start upgrading.<br>
<br>
Also leaves you enough to buy some bags -<br>
1. Evil eye bag 400pp<br>
2. Archeologist pack 400pp<br>
3. Herbalist pack 400pp<br>
4. (5) 10 slot tailored backpacks 400pp<br>
<br>
Which will leave you 50pp for food and water. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Wizard of the 47th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
